 Earlier, the Nigerian Guild of Editors (NGE) in a statement signed by its General Secretary, Mary Atolagbe, rejected the new guidelines.https://sundiatapost.com/2019/05/20/nigerian-guild-of-editors-rejects-national-assembly-guidelines-for-journalists-accreditation/. The NGE described the guidelines as  “as primitive, undemocratic and blatantly anti-press and anti-people.”